<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="ITA19">
<l>vaḻakkaṉṟu kaṇṭāy valicakaṭañ ceṟṟāy</l>
<l>vaḻakkeṉṟu nīmatikka vēṇṭā – kuḻakkaṉṟu</l>
<l>tīviḷaviṉ kāykkeṟinta tīmai tirumālē</l>
<l>pārviḷaṅkac ceytāy paḻi</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>It is not [good] conduct<note xml:lang="en" place="foot">For the first instance of a nindāstuti verse, see Pū. 15.</note>; look, you who destroyed the strong cart,</l>
<l>you need not think it is [good] conduct, evil Tirumāl</l>
<l>who threw the young calf after the fruits of the evil wood-apple tree</l>
<l>– you committed a crime, so that it is evident to the world.</l>
      </lg>
    </div>
